  <div class="faq">
    <details>
      <summary>Why use a 9% discount rate?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">The 10-year Treasury yields 4.18%. While defense primes are generally lower risk (lower beta) due to the government being the primary customer, L3Harris currently carries almost $12B in debt. A 9% WACC balances the stability of the revenues with the financial risk of the balance sheet.</div>
    </details>
    <details>
      <summary>Why 6% FCF growth?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer">L3Harris has a massive backlog and is seeing expanding margins as older, less profitable contracts burn off. We project 6% as a blend of mid-single-digit revenue growth and modest margin expansion over the next five years.</div>
    </details>
